 derived quantities, such as the radius, surface gravity, and seismic\nindices. We demonstrate that SPInS can age-date and characterise coeval stars\nthat share a common age and chemical composition. The SPInS tool will be very\nhelpful in preparing and interpreting the results of large-scale surveys, such\nas the wealth of data expected or already provided by space missions, such as\nGaia, Kepler, TESS, and PLATO.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 31 Aug 2020 18:05:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-14"}
